verses.text_plain: Now the word of the Lord came unto Jonah the son of Amittai, saying,
verses.verse_html:
1Now the word of the Lord came unto Jonah the son of Amittai, saying, ▼
▼ Jonah: Gr. Jonas

verses.text_plain: Arise, go to Nineveh, that great city, and cry against it; for their wickedness is come up before me.
verses.verse_html: 2Arise, go to Nineveh, that great city, and cry against it; for their wickedness is come up before me.

verses.text_plain: But Jonah rose up to flee unto Tarshish from the presence of the Lord, and went down to Joppa; and he found a ship going to Tarshish: so he paid the fare thereof, and went down into it, to go with them unto Tarshish from the presence of the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 3But Jonah rose up to flee unto Tarshish from the presence of the Lord, and went down to Joppa; and he found a ship going to Tarshish: so he paid the fare thereof, and went down into it, to go with them unto Tarshish from the presence of the Lord.

verses.text_plain: But the Lord sent out a great wind into the sea, and there was a mighty tempest in the sea, so that the ship was like to be broken.
verses.verse_html:
4But the Lord sent out a great wind into the sea, and there was a mighty tempest in the sea, so that the ship was like to be broken. ▼
▼ sent out: Heb. cast forth
 , ▼
▼ was like…: Heb. thought to be broken

footnotes.body_html: ▼ sent out: Heb. cast forth

footnotes.body_text: ▼ was like…: Heb. thought to be broken
footnotes.body_html: ▼ was like…: Heb. thought to be broken

verses.text_plain: Then the mariners were afraid, and cried every man unto his god, and cast forth the wares that were in the ship into the sea, to lighten it of them. But Jonah was gone down into the sides of the ship; and he lay, and was fast asleep.
verses.verse_html: 5Then the mariners were afraid, and cried every man unto his god, and cast forth the wares that were in the ship into the sea, to lighten it of them. But Jonah was gone down into the sides of the ship; and he lay, and was fast asleep.

verses.text_plain: So the shipmaster came to him, and said unto him, What meanest thou, O sleeper? arise, call upon thy God, if so be that God will think upon us, that we perish not.
verses.verse_html: 6So the shipmaster came to him, and said unto him, What meanest thou, O sleeper? arise, call upon thy God, if so be that God will think upon us, that we perish not.

tokens.text: unto him, What meanest thou, O sleeper

verses.text_plain: And they said every one to his fellow, Come, and let us cast lots, that we may know for whose cause this evil is upon us. So they cast lots, and the lot fell upon Jonah.
verses.verse_html: 7And they said every one to his fellow, Come, and let us cast lots, that we may know for whose cause this evil is upon us. So they cast lots, and the lot fell upon Jonah.

verses.text_plain: Then said they unto him, Tell us, we pray thee, for whose cause this evil is upon us; What is thine occupation? and whence comest thou? what is thy country? and of what people art thou?
verses.verse_html: 8Then said they unto him, Tell us, we pray thee, for whose cause this evil is upon us; What is thine occupation? and whence comest thou? what is thy country? and of what people art thou?

tokens.text: us, we pray thee, for whose cause this evil

verses.text_plain: And he said unto them, I am an Hebrew; and I fear the Lord, the God of heaven, which hath made the sea and the dry land.
verses.verse_html:
9And he said unto them, I am an Hebrew; and I fear the Lord, the God of heaven, which hath made the sea and the dry land. ▼
▼ the Lord: or, Jehovah

verses.text_plain: Then were the men exceedingly afraid, and said unto him, Why hast thou done this? For the men knew that he fled from the presence of the Lord, because he had told them.
verses.verse_html:
10Then were the men exceedingly afraid, and said unto him, Why hast thou done this? For the men knew that he fled from the presence of the Lord, because he had told them. ▼
▼ exceedingly…: Heb. with great fear

tokens.text: unto him, Why hast thou done

footnotes.body_html: ▼ exceedingly…: Heb. with great fear

verses.text_plain: Then said they unto him, What shall we do unto thee, that the sea may be calm unto us? for the sea wrought, and was tempestuous.
verses.verse_html:
11Then said they unto him, What shall we do unto thee, that the sea may be calm unto us? for the sea wrought, and was tempestuous. ▼
▼ may…: Heb. may be silent from us
 , ▼
▼ wrought…: or, grew more and more tempestuous: Heb. went

tokens.text: they unto him, What shall we do

footnotes.body_text: ▼ may…: Heb. may be silent from us
footnotes.body_html: ▼ may…: Heb. may be silent from us

footnotes.body_text: ▼ wrought…: or, grew more and more tempestuous: Heb. went
footnotes.body_html: ▼ wrought…: or, grew more and more tempestuous: Heb. went

verses.text_plain: And he said unto them, Take me up, and cast me forth into the sea; so shall the sea be calm unto you: for I know that for my sake this great tempest is upon you.
verses.verse_html: 12And he said unto them, Take me up, and cast me forth into the sea; so shall the sea be calm unto you: for I know that for my sake this great tempest is upon you.

verses.text_plain: Nevertheless the men rowed hard to bring it to the land; but they could not: for the sea wrought, and was tempestuous against them.
verses.verse_html:
13Nevertheless the men rowed hard to bring it to the land; but they could not: for the sea wrought, and was tempestuous against them. ▼
▼ rowed: Heb. digged
 , ▼
▼ wrought…: or, grew more and more tempestuous: Heb. went

footnotes.body_text: ▼ wrought…: or, grew more and more tempestuous: Heb. went
footnotes.body_html: ▼ wrought…: or, grew more and more tempestuous: Heb. went

verses.text_plain: Wherefore they cried unto the Lord, and said, We beseech thee, O Lord, we beseech thee, let us not perish for this man’s life, and lay not upon us innocent blood: for thou, O Lord, hast done as it pleased thee.
verses.verse_html: 14Wherefore they cried unto the Lord, and said, We beseech thee, O Lord, we beseech thee, let us not perish for this man’s life, and lay not upon us innocent blood: for thou, O Lord, hast done as it pleased thee.

tokens.text: we beseech thee, let us not perish

verses.text_plain: So they took up Jonah, and cast him forth into the sea: and the sea ceased from her raging.
verses.verse_html:
15So they took up Jonah, and cast him forth into the sea: and the sea ceased from her raging. ▼
▼ ceased: Heb. stood

verses.text_plain: Then the men feared the Lord exceedingly, and offered a sacrifice unto the Lord, and made vows.
verses.verse_html:
16Then the men feared the Lord exceedingly, and offered a sacrifice unto the Lord, and made vows. ▼
▼ offered…: Heb. sacrifice unto the Lord, and vowed vows

footnotes.body_text: ▼ offered…: Heb. sacrifice unto the Lord, and vowed vows
footnotes.body_html: ▼ offered…: Heb. sacrifice unto the Lord, and vowed vows

verses.text_plain: Now the Lord had prepared a great fish to swallow up Jonah. And Jonah was in the belly of the fish three days and three nights.
verses.verse_html:
17Now the Lord had prepared a great fish to swallow up Jonah. And Jonah was in the belly of the fish three days and three nights. ▼
▼ belly: Heb. bowels
